<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Add Runner - Winter 100</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@picocss/pico@2/css/pico.min.css">
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@2.0.2"></script>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/static/images/logo.svg">
    <style>
        .welcome-section {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 2rem;
            border-radius: var(--pico-border-radius);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .color-preview {
            width: 20px;
            height: 20px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: inline-block;
            margin-left: 0.5rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="container">
        <ul>
            <li><strong><a href="/"><img src="/static/images/logo.svg" alt="Winter100 Logo" style="height:2rem;width:2rem;"> Winter 100</a></strong></li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/logout">Logout</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <main class="container">
        <div class="welcome-section">
            <h1>Welcome to Winter 100!</h1>
            <p>Your family account has been created successfully. Now let's create your first runner account.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid">
            <div></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Create Your Runner Account</h2>
                <p>A runner account tracks your individual miles and progress. You can create multiple runner accounts for each family member.</p>
                
                <form hx-post="/create-runner" hx-target="#runner-response">
                    <div>
                        <label for="name">Runner Name</label>
                        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" placeholder="Enter your name" required maxlength="50">
                        <small>This is the name that will appear on the leaderboard.</small>
                    </div>
                    

                    
                    <button type="submit">Create Runner Account</button>
                </form>
                
                <div id="runner-response"></div>
                
                <hr>
                
                <p><small>After creating your runner account, you'll be taken to your dashboard where you can start logging miles!</small></p>
            </div>
            <div></div>
        </div>
    </main>


</body>
</html>
